    <item>
      <title>NSERC CRD Award: 3D Object Recognition for Museum Exhibits</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/news/nserc-crd-simentit-2017/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 05 Oct 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/news/nserc-crd-simentit-2017/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Dr. Naimul Khan, Dr. Ling Guan, and Dr. Andy Ye have been awarded a $375,000 NSERC Collaborative Research and Development Grant in partnership with &lt;a href=&#34;https://simentit.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;SimentIT Inc.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This two-year project will develop novel 3D object recognition and tracking algorithms for museum augmented reality exhibits. The technology will be deployed at the newly renovated &lt;a href=&#34;https://ingeniumcanada.org/sciencetech&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Canada Science and Technology Museum&lt;/a&gt; in Ottawa, enabling visitors to experience interactive AR overlays on physical artifacts.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
